div1.p:
Whether these men were acquaintances of yours or not? - I did not know them except two of them; I have heard their names mentioned; I knew nothing of them before; Kilby might know them; Kilby told me they were all there; there were none of the men in the house when Kilby came in; Kilby and I had a pint of purl; we sat there drinking it;
Jack Kilby
said to me, I think I hear a window break; Woodmore and Wiley came in and were playing at the devil and the tailors, as they call it.
